SUMMARY:The Long Game: Artist Development\, Community\, & Career Sustainabi
 lity
LOCATION:Capital Factory\, Austin\, TX
DESCRIPTION:Source: Luma\n\nThe music industry often celebrates breakthroug
 hs\, viral moments\, and success stories\; but what does it actually take 
 to build a sustainable career over the long term?\n\nJoin Prosper XO for a
 n evening exploring artist development\, community\, career sustainability
 \, building a business\, and the support systems that help artists grow\, 
 evolve\, and thrive.\n\nFrom artist management and record labels to nonpro
 fit support and community infrastructure\, we'll discuss the realities of 
 building a lasting career in music\, the challenges artists face along the
  way\, and what it takes to create an ecosystem where artists can succeed 
 not just for a moment\; but for a lifetime.\n\nWhether you're an artist\, 
 manager\, entrepreneur\, student\, industry professional\, or passionate s
 upporter of the arts\, this conversation is for you.\n\n📅 Wednesday\, J
 uly 8th | 6–8:30 PM\n\nThis event is free and open to the public.\n\nFea
 turing:\n\nJustin Weems\nFounder\, FSG | FSG Records\n\nJustin Weems is a 
 founder of FSG\, a Texas-based apparel brand\, community\, and creative mo
 vement that has grown into a platform supporting artists\, culture\, and i
 ndependent expression. He is also a founder of FSG Records\, where he work
 s to develop artists\, build sustainable careers\, and create opportunitie
 s that extend beyond traditional industry models. Through both FSG and FSG
  Records\, Justin has helped cultivate a community-driven approach to arti
 st development rooted in authenticity\, creativity\, and long-term growth.
 \n\nJazz Mills\nCEO\, Free Lunch | Artist Manager | Artist\n\nJazz Mills i
 s the CEO of Free Lunch\, artist manager\, and longtime performing artist 
 whose career has given her firsthand experience navigating the realities o
 f the music industry from multiple perspectives. Through her work as both 
 an artist and advocate\, she understands the challenges creatives face whi
 le building sustainable careers. Today\, she works to support artists thro
 ugh management\, community-building\, education\, and the creation of oppo
 rtunities that help artists thrive both creatively and professionally.\n\n
 Hosted by:\n\nLauren Bruno & Prosper XO\n\nProsper XO is an artist-first e
 thical technology company and education + cultural initiative focused on a
 rtist sustainability\, creative autonomy\, ownership\, and community build
 ing. Through monthly Town Halls\, Prosper XO brings together artists\, ind
 ustry leaders\, educators\, researchers\, entrepreneurs\, and community me
 mbers to explore the future of creativity\, culture\, and artist prosperit
 y.\n\nAt Prosper XO\, we believe artists are essential cultural partners. 
 We believe value created by the creative community should help strengthen 
 the creative community. And we believe that when artists have access to th
 e support\, resources\, opportunities\, and relationships they need to thr
 ive\, entire communities benefit.\n\nExpect networking\, meaningful conver
 sation\, new connections\, and a room full of people passionate about buil
 ding a stronger future for artists.\n\nBecause success isn't built overnig
 ht.\n\nAnd when artists prosper\, culture thrives.\n\nLogistical Details\n
 \nParking Discount: Park in the Omni Hotel garage below Capital Factory an
 d pick up a voucher at the event for a reduced $8 fee.\n\nLocation: ACL Ro
 om – 16th Floor\, Capital Factory\n701 Brazos St\, Austin\, TX 78701\n\n
 Special Thanks\n\nThank you to Station Austin for sponsoring Prosper XO. S
 tation Austin is the center of gravity for entrepreneurs in Texas\, connec
 ting founders with investors\, mentors\, employees\, and customers.\n\nTha
 nk you to Free Lunch for their partnership and continued commitment to sup
 porting artists and creative communities.\n\nStay Connected\n\nJoin our ma
 iling list for updates & future events:\nhttps://mailchi.mp/d31733a7aa36/p
 rosperxo\n\nWant to speak at an upcoming Town Hall?\nWant to sponsor a fut
 ure event?\nEmail: lauren@prosperxo.com\n\nFollow Prosper XO:\nInstagram\n
 LinkedIn \nX \nTikTok\nYouTube\n\n🌈💗✊🎶\n\nCalendar: Personal\n\
 nHosts: Prosper XO\n\nVenue: Capital Factory\n\nEvent page: https://luma.c
 om/ju3d23tb
URL:https://luma.com/ju3d23tb
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
