SUMMARY:Austin | Claude Code Meetup
LOCATION:Capital Factory\, Austin\, TX
DESCRIPTION:Source: Luma\n\nWelcome to Claude Code Austin!\n\nThanks to eve
 ryone who has been coming out to our events!   \n\nWe're back with our Jul
 y edition of Claude Code Austin. This meetup is created to help connect th
 e local community and learn more about using Claude. Thank you to everyone
  who has provided great feedback on our past events.\n\n6:00 PM - 6:25 PM 
 - Doors Open & Networking\nGrab some refreshments and connect with local b
 uilders.\n\n6:25 PM - 6:30 PM - Event Welcome\n\n6:30 PM - 7:10 PM - Prese
 nters\nWe'll hear from 3 builders showcasing projects they've created usin
 g Claude Code. If you're interested in presenting please complete this for
 m.\nNote we have limited slots available for demo presentations. We give h
 igh consideration to any demo that helps our attendees learn tactics for b
 uilding with Claude Code.\n\n7:10 PM - 8:00 PM - Breakout Sessions \nOur g
 roup will break out in smaller volunteer led sessions on specific topics r
 elated to Claude Code. If you're interested in leading a breakout session 
 please complete this form. \n\n8:00 PM - Wrap Up and Closing\nFinal wrap u
 p and closing.\n\nA special thank you to Station Austin for sponsoring Cla
 ude Code Meetup Austin. STATION Austin is the center of gravity for entrep
 reneurs in Texas. Day and night\, in-person and online\, we gather the bes
 t founders\, programmers\, and designers outside of Silicon Valley and int
 roduce them to investors\, employees\, and customers who help their ideas 
 launch. STATION Austin is powered by Capital Factory\, whose investments a
 nd leadership have helped power the Texas startup ecosystem for more than 
 a decade. To sign up for a STATION Austin membership\, click here.\n\nCale
 ndar: Claude Community Events\n\nHosts: Claude Community\, Damon Bodine\n\
 nVenue: Capital Factory\n\nEvent page: https://luma.com/claude-3p50
URL:https://luma.com/claude-3p50
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:evt-aek9smC9YJyxjuw@luma.com
DTSTAMP:20260706T020844Z
DTSTART:20260714T223000Z
DTEND:20260715T003000Z
SUMMARY:AI that works: Apify + TwelveLabs
LOCATION:Antler VC\, Austin\, TX
DESCRIPTION:Source: Luma\n\nAI that works is a monthly meetup for anyone bu
 ilding with AI in Austin: developers\, founders\, operators\, go-to-market
  (GTM) teams\, and the AI-curious. Every session: live demos from people s
 hipping real things\, a hands-on build\, and honest conversation about wha
 t's actually producing results.\n\nWe don't care if you're writing code or
  mostly prompting. If you're putting AI to work on something real\, you be
 long here.\n\nThis month\n\nWe'll build a competitor ad-spy tool that turn
 s hours of manual scrolling through the Meta Ad Library into a paste-one-U
 RL workflow. You give it a competitor's Facebook page\, and it pulls their
  video ads\, ranks them by the spend and longevity signals that reveal a l
 ikely winner\, and has AI watch each one to reverse-engineer the creative 
 strategy: hook\, offer\, proof\, and call to action (CTA).\n\nIf you run p
 aid social\, you'll leave knowing how to surface a competitor's winning ad
 s and the structure behind them. If you build with AI\, you'll leave with 
 the full stack: an Apify Actor that orchestrates a scraper\, a scoring mod
 el\, and four different AI models into one tool.\n\nHow the evening works\
 n\nWe start with why studying competitor ads by hand doesn't work: you scr
 oll the Ad Library\, watch dozens of videos one at a time\, screenshot hoo
 ks into a doc you never reopen\, and you're still guessing which ads are a
 ctually winning. Then we build the tool that does it for you.\n\nFirst\, t
 he data layer. We wrap apify/facebook-ads-scraper inside a single new Acto
 r that pulls up to 100 ads per page with public metadata - active status\,
  run duration\, placements\, variants\, and spend signals - then scores an
 d ranks them so the high-conviction ads float to the top.\n\nNext\, the an
 alysis layer. We pass the top-ranked videos to TwelveLabs: Pegasus 1.5 ret
 urns a structured creative blueprint (hook\, audience\, problem framing\, 
 offer\, proof\, CTA\, pacing\, and scene-by-scene notes)\, and Marengo 3.0
  indexes each video so you can query it later. Gemini then synthesizes a c
 ross-competitor report on the patterns across hooks\, visual styles\, offe
 rs\, and CTAs.\n\nFinally\, the interrogation layer. We wire up a split-sc
 reen video-and-chat view powered by Claude Sonnet\, ask it "show me the ho
 ok" or "where's the CTA?"\, and click any returned timestamp to seek the v
 ideo straight to that frame.\n\nYou'll leave with a working composite Acto
 r in your Apify account and a repeatable pattern for orchestrating multipl
 e models behind one clean input and one useful output.\n\nBring your lapto
 p.\n\nAgenda\n\n5:30 pm - doors open and networking\n\n5:45 pm - kickoff a
 nd presentation\n\n6:00 pm - workshop\n\n7:15 pm - wrap-up and chatting\n\
 n7:30 pm - end\n\nWhat you'll need for the hands-on portion\n\nA laptop (m
 acOS\, Windows\, or Linux)\n\nAn Apify account (free tier or higher) with 
 enough platform usage left in the month to run workflows live\n\nNode.js i
 nstalled\n\nYour preferred code editor (Cursor\, VS Code\, or similar)\n\n
 Some comfort with the terminal and basic JavaScript/TypeScript - you don't
  need to be an expert\, but you'll be editing code during the build\n\nDon
 't have all of this? No worries\, you can follow along with someone at the
  event who does. The concepts apply regardless of your stack.\n\nAbout the
  host\n\nApify is the platform behind thousands of ready-to-use tools that
  give AI agents and apps access to web data\, automation\, and real-world 
 information. But this meetup isn't a product pitch\, it's a community. See
  what people are building\, learn something new\, and meet the people doin
 g the work.\n\n👾 Join the conversation on Discord.\n\nExplore Apify at 
 apify.com.\n\nWe will use your information to contact you about the event.
  For more information\, see our Privacy Policy.\n\nCalendar: Apify Events\
 n\nHosts: Apify\n\nVenue: Antler VC\n\nEvent page: https://luma.com/apify-
 r3b3
URL:https://luma.com/apify-r3b3
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
